ACS, Iberdrola, Obrascon Huarte Lain: Iberian Equity Preview

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-05-25T04:00:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/acs-iberdrola-obrascon-huarte-lain-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain ’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  gained 0.3 percent to 10,115.90.
Portugal’s PSI-20 Index fell 0.1 percent to 7,595.32.  Spanish stocks:       Actividades de Construccion y Servicios SA (ACS SM): Grupo
Dragados SA, a unit of Spain’s biggest construction company, is
offering to increase the interest margin on a loan signed in
2009 in order to extend its maturity by two years, according to
two people with knowledge of the situation. The shares gained
0.8 percent to 32.19 euros.  Iberdrola SA (IBE)  ,: The Spanish power company which
counts ACS as its biggest shareholder will propose to
shareholders this week that it pay its ordinary 2010 dividend of
3 euro cents per share on July 13. The shares rose less than 0.1
percent to 5.97 euros.  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL)  : The Spanish construction
company said it will pay an ordinary dividend of 49 euro cents
per share from June 1. The shares rose 1.1 percent to 24.94
euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net  